=2016-12-20|website=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/pegasus-nso-group-iphone-2016-8|title=Inside 'Pegasus,' the impossible-to-detect software that hacks your iPhone|accessdate=2016-12-21|date=2016-08-26|last=Szoldra|first=Paul|publisher=[[Axel_Springer_SE|Axel Springer SE]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221162145/http://www.businessinsider.com/pegasus-nso-group-iphone-2016-8|archivedate=2016-12-21|website=[[Business_Insider|Business Insider]]|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/iphone-hack-pegasus-malware-security-ios-update-1201845700/|title=This App Can Tell if an iPhone Was Hacked With Latest Pegasus Spy Malware|accessdate=2016-12-21|date=2016-08-26|last=Roettgers|first=Janko|publisher=[[Penske_Media_Corporation|Penske Media Corporation]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221162858/http://variety.com/2016/digital/news/iphone-hack-pegasus-malware-security-ios-update-1201845700/|archivedate=2016-12-21|website=[[Variety_(magazine)|Variety]]|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/2016/08/hacking-group-selling-ios-vulnerabilities-state-actors/|title=A Hacking Group Is Selling iPhone Spyware to Governments|accessdate=2016-12-21|date=2016-08-25|last=Newman|first=Lily Hay|publisher=[[Condé_Nast|Condé Nast]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221163133/https://www.wired.com/2016/08/hacking-group-selling-ios-vulnerabilities-state-actors/|archivedate=2016-12-21|website=[[Wired_(website)|Wired]]|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2016/08/25/apple-issues-security-update-prevent-iphone-spyware/89347242/|title=Apple issues security update to prevent iPhone spyware|accessdate=2016-12-21|date=2016-08-26|publisher=[[Gannett_Company|Gannett Company]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160830100432/http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2016/08/25/apple-issues-security-upd